    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_29",
    "text": "A-5 We may discard any solutions for which a # az, since those come in pairs; so assume a1 = a2. Similarly, we may assume that a3 = a4, as = a6, a7 = a8, ao = a10. Thus we get the equation",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
