  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_14",
    "text": "We claim then that the game terminates if and only if the number of players is a power of 2. First suppose the number of players is even; then after m complete rounds, every other player, starting with the player who moved first, will have m more pennies than initially, and the others will all have 0. Thus we are reduced to the situation with half as many players; by this process, we eventually reduce to the case where the number of players is odd. However, if there is more than one player, after two complete rounds everyone has as many pennies as they did before (here we need m ≥ 2), so the game fails to terminate. This verifies the claim.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.1278195442882287,
      0.7107558146005595,
      0.49060151260400175,
      0.8822674414071926
    ],
    "page": "exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001",
    "order": 32
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_31",
    "text": "Again, we may assume a1 = a3 and as = a7, so we get 4/a1 + 4/as + 2/a, = 1; and a1 = as, so 8/a1 + 2/ao = 1. This implies that (a1 - 8) (ao - 2) = 16, which by counting has 5 solutions. Thus Nio is odd.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.556390976632824,
      0.717808066641337,
      0.9211463261920722,
      0.7748015873714286
    ],
    "page": "exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001",
    "order": 33
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_32",
    "text": "A-6 Clearly n+1 is a polynomial in c of degree n, so it suffices to identify n values of c for which n+1 = 0. We claim these are c = n - 1 - 2r for r = 0,1,...,n - 1; in this case, xk is the coefficient of pk-' in the polynomial f(t) = (1 - t)\"(1 +t)\"-1-*. This can be verified by noticing that f satisfies the differential equation",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5244360918934675,
      0.7863372093019254,
      0.9210526404235507,
      0.8720930230447893
