    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_15",
    "text": "Returning to the original game, note that after one complete round, (\"-' J players remain, each with 2 pennies except for the player to move, who has either 3 or 4 pennies. Thus by the above argument, the game terminates if and only if |\"2' J is a power of 2, that is, if and only if n = 2m + 1 or n = 2m + 2 for some m.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
